  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "70-year-old retired man presents with low grade fever, painless swelling in the neck and fatigue for the past 3 months. Examination reveals generalized lymphadenopathy and mild splenomegaly. CBC shows WBC 85,000/µL with absolute lymphocyte count 65,000/µL. Peripheral smear shows numerous small mature-appearing lymphocytes and smudge cells. Which of the following is the investigation of choice to confirm the diagnosis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Peripheral blood flow cytometry"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Bone marrow aspiration showing lymphoblasts > 20%"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "FISH analysis for 17p deletion"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "PCR for ZAP-70 expression"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is A: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"255674f3271692777195c172d86daf\">Peripheral</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"82cc227a1c169277718387905b50c6\">blood flow</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"551a62b1ec169277718587f847e627\">cytometry</span> </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>CLL diagnosis is made by demonstrating a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> B-cell population with CLL <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"09f070cb5e16927771891083cd1747\">immunophenotype</span> (CD19+, CD20dim, CD5+, CD23+) using flow <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"551a62b1ec169277718587f847e627\">cytometry</span> on <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"255674f3271692777195c172d86daf\">peripheral</span> blood.</li>\n\t<li>Bone <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c8a8c935a41692777191610f6aacb4\">marrow</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"831d67ad8a1692777182763ca62e4b\">aspiration</span> showing lymphoblasts > 20% is cut off for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">acute</span> leukemia</li>\n\t<li>FISH and PCR for ZAP-70 are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfb6c738351692777196f69788a66e\">prognostic</span> markers, not first-line <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> tests.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "A 65-year-old man on an annual medical check-up is found to have lymphocytosis on routine CBC (total leukocyte count: 11,000/µL; absolute lymphocyte count: 4,200/µL). He is asymptomatic with no lymphadenopathy or organomegaly. Peripheral smear shows mature-appearing small lymphocytes. Flow cytometry reveals a monoclonal B-cell population with CLL immunophenotype. Which of the following features will help distinguish this condition from CLL?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Presence of B symptoms"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Absolute B-cell count < 5 × 10⁹/L"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Positive Coombs test"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Expression of CD19, CD20, CD5"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is b: Absolute B Cell count < 5x10</strong><strong><sup>9</sup></strong><strong>/L</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Monoclonal B-cell <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3a521c75816927771913d4e993e2d\">lymphocytosis</span> (MBL)</strong> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"feb5b6aaeb16927771964c9d7c801c\">premalignant</span> condition characterized by a small population of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> B cells in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"255674f3271692777195c172d86daf\">peripheral</span> blood <strong>< 5 × 10⁹/L</strong>, with CLL-like immunophenotype, <strong>no lymphadenopathy, hepatosplenomegaly, or cytopenias</strong>.</li>\n\t<li><strong>CLL diagnosis</strong> requires <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> B-cell count <strong>≥ 5 × 10⁹/L</strong> or tissue infiltration.</li>\n\t<li>CD19, CD20, CD5 expression occurs in both MBL and CLL, so it does not help differentiate.</li>\n\t<li>Presence of B symptoms or cytopenias would favor CLL.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Radiation exposure is associated with increased risk of several hematological malignancies. Which of the following is least likely to be related to radiation exposure",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "ALL"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "AML"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "CML"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "CLL"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is d: CLL</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Radiation is not a risk factor for CLL.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following peripheral smear findings is not seen in CLL?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Spherocytes"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Smudge cells"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Prolymphocytes"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Lymphoblasts"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is d: Lymphoblasts </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Lymphoblasts are a hallmark of ALL and not CLL</li>\n\t<li><strong>CLL <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"255674f3271692777195c172d86daf\">peripheral</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6777533153169277719804fcbbf2d1\">smear</span> findings</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><strong>Small <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0472620c171692777192c655af9c57\">mature</span> lymphocytes</strong></li>\n\t<li><strong>Smudge cells</strong> (fragile lymphocytes)</li>\n\t<li><strong>Prolymphocytes</strong> (< 55%)</li>\n\t<li><strong>Spherocytes</strong> can appear if <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> develops as a complication.</li>\n</ol>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following statements regarding Richter transformation is correct?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Transformation of CLL into diffuse large B-cell lymphoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Transformation of follicular lymphoma into diffuse large B-cell lymphoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Transformation of marginal zone lymphoma into diffuse large B-cell lymphoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Transformation of mantle cell lymphoma into diffuse large B-cell lymphoma"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Transformation of CLL into <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"89275101301692777186567d1912a0\">diffuse</span> large B-Cell Lymphoma</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Remember Ritcher transformation as “Rich CLL turns bold” ie CLL transformation into new avatar as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"89275101301692777186567d1912a0\">diffuse</span> large B cell lymphoma.</li>\n\t<li>Follicular lymphoma, marginal zone lymphoma, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ec65d4890169277719136decb922c\">mantle</span> cell <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5a31d184f21692777191a2e457d646\">lymphoma</span> can all transform into DLBCL, but these are <strong>not</strong> called Richter transformation — they are simply termed <strong>histologic transformations</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Leading cause of death in patients diagnosed with CLL?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Hypo-gammaglobulinemia"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Heart disease"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Kidney failure"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Hyper viscosity syndrome"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Hypo-gammaglobulinemia</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>In CLL, B cells are monoclonal, abnormal, and do not mount proper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d7a12cab116927771811a0079086d\">antibody</span> responses.</li>\n\t<li>They also dysregulate the immune system, sometimes producing autoantibodies against the patient’s own red cells or platelets causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> haemolytic anaemia and ITP.</li>\n\t<li>With progressive decline in functional immunoglobulins, patients become especially vulnerable to encapsulated bacteria (e.g., Streptococcus pneumoniae, Haemophilus influenzae), as well as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5cc2d9fac616927772021889ee6d52\">viral</span> reactivations.</li>\n</ul>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Known case of CLL is admitted with shortness of breath on minimal activity. Work up shows Hb= 7 gm%, TLC 25000 cells/cu.mm, platelet count of 50K/cu.mm, reticulocyte count is 2% with low haptoglobin and elevated LDH. Which of the following test would help in further evaluation of this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Direct coombs test"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "ZAP-70"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "FISH"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Treadmill test"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Direct coombs test</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>CLL can be complicated by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> haemolytic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> thrombocytopenia.</li>\n\t<li>Laboratory signs of hemolysis: low haptoglobin, elevated LDH, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> with reticulocytosis.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Direct Coombs (Direct antiglobulin) test</strong> detects antibodies (usually warm IgG) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d82fcb9d1f16927771836a9f6ccf14\">bound</span> to RBCs, <strong>confirming <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> etiology</strong>.</li>\n\t<li>ZAP-70 and FISH are for <strong>prognosis</strong>, not <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">acute</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> clarification.</li>\n\t<li>Treadmill test is unrelated to this presentation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following is drug used in CLL acts is inhibitor of antiapoptotic protein BCL2?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Venetoclax"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Ibrutinib"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Idelalisib"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Duvelisib"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Venetoclax</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:505px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Option</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Mechanism of action </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Venetoclax</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>inhibitor of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"40b34ad60b1692777181d8b83d0685\">antiapoptotic</span> protein BCL2 and promotes apoptosis</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Ibrutinib</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>BTK inhibitor: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9dc12b322016927771830dff673eeb\">blocking</span> B-cell <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9e4959f6f316927771978bb152d440\">receptor</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f9016f36fd1692777198b0fd5e9c6d\">signaling</span> that inhibits B-cell <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8eedb6cec61692777196a6a3b93d3f\">proliferation</span> and survival</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Idelalisib</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>PI3K inhibitor: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9dc12b322016927771830dff673eeb\">blocking</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f5467ab59316927771863c852a23a6\">downstream</span> survival pathways (AKT/mTOR) that induces <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4bfa3e6f2c1692777181c53b124cf7\">apoptosis</span> and reduces <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4c550b1d7a1692777200641b5f4e28\">trafficking</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f8aaf091221692777191f73e810e94\">malignant</span> B-cells</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Duvelisib</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>PI3K inhibitor: same as above</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
