    {
      "text": "Evan syndrome is defined as?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Autoimmune hemolytic anemia + autoimmune thrombocytopenia"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Autoimmune hemolytic anemia + autoimmune granulocytopenia"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Pure red cell aplasia + autoimmune granulocytopenia"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Pure red cell aplasia + autoimmune thrombocytopenia"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">Autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> + <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">Autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc28c74bb716927772003aee4aa43c\">thrombocytopenia</span> </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Evan’s syndrome is coexistence (simultaneous or sequential) of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> anemia<strong> </strong>and immune thrombocytopenia. It can occur idiopathically or secondary to conditions like SLE and CLL.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following is not a component of Rai staging system used in CLL?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Lymphocytosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Lymphadenopathy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Hepatosplenomegaly"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Autoimmune hemolytic anemia"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is d: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">Autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> anemia</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>It is anaemia or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc28c74bb716927772003aee4aa43c\">thrombocytopenia</span> caused by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b9831f3aa169277718395d7361df6\">bone marrow</span> involvement that is considered and not <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96ab11a06a16927771823151c8e471\">autoimmune</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> anaemia.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Staging of CLL</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Rai Staging System</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>Low risk (stage 0)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>Lymphocytosis only</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>Intermediate risk (stage I/II)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>Lymphocytosis with lymphadenopathy, with or without <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b3eb52fe3b1692777199de8465eea8\">splenomegaly</span> or hepatomegaly</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>High risk (stage III/IV)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:none; vertical-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<p>Lymphocytosis with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc28c74bb716927772003aee4aa43c\">thrombocytopenia</span> due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b9831f3aa169277718395d7361df6\">bone marrow</span> involvement</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
